Basic istallation procedure to install a Puppet Master

commands must issued with root privilege. If you don't have it use sudo

1. install the repo in order to get the latest puppet relase
 1.a rehl 6:
   - rpm -ivh http://yum.puppetlabs.com/puppetlabs-release-el-6.noarch.rpm
 1.b rehl 7:
   - rpm -ivh http://yum.puppetlabs.com/puppetlabs-release-el-7.noarch.rpm
 1.c ubuntu:
   - wget https://apt.puppetlabs.com/puppetlabs-release-<CODE NAME>.deb
   - dpkg -i puppetlabs-release-precise.deb
   - apt-get update

2. Install puppet master
 - yum/apt-get install puppet-server

3. Download all the configuration files in the config dir on this repo into /etc/puppet dir
   on your puppet master host. You don't need to modify them

4. Start the puppet master
 - service puppetmaster start
 - service puppetmaster status

5. Check puppetmaster network port status
 - telent localhsot 8140
